1 Vall ey, Pauls Valley, Oklahoma; Western State Psychiatric Center,
2 Fort Supply, Oklahoma; Central Oklahoma Juvenile Treatment Center,
3 Tecumseh, Oklahoma; L.E. Rader Children's Diagnostic and Evaluation
4 Center, Sand Springs, Oklahoma; L.E. Rader Intensive Treatment
5 Center, Sand Springs, Oklahoma; the Southwest Oklahoma Juvenile
6 Center, Manitou, Oklahoma; the Office of Juvenile Affairs' Boys'
7 Group Home, Enid, Oklahoma; the Office of Juvenile Affairs' Boys'
8 Group Home, Lawton, Oklahoma; the Office of Juvenile Affairs' Girls'
9 Group Home, Tulsa, Oklahoma; the Oklahoma Medical Center; and the
10 J.D. McCarty Center for Children with Developmental Disabilities.
11 2. The Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
12 Services and the head of the institution involved are hereby
13 authorized and it shall be their duty to fix the maximum amount of
14 the petty cash funds. The Director of the Office of Management and
15 Enterprise Services shall prescribe all forms, systems, and
16 procedures for administering the petty cash funds of the
17 institution.
18 B. 1. There is hereby created a petty cash fund in the legal
19 division of the Department of Human Services which fund shall be
20 used solely to pay court costs, filing fees, witness fees, and
21 expenses related to any case or proceeding within the responsibility
22 of the legal division.
23 2. There is hereby created a petty cash fund in the Child
24 Support Enforcement Division of the Department of Human Services.
HB3466 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 The fund shall be used solely to pay litigation expenses, including
2 court costs, filing fees, witness fees, and expenses related to any
3 case or proceeding within the responsibility of the Child Support
4 Enforcement Division.
5 3. The Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
6 Services and the Director of the Department of Human Services are
7 hereby authorized and it shall be their duty to fix the maximum
8 amount of the petty cash funds. The Director of the Office of
9 Management and Enterprise Services shall prescribe all forms,
10 systems, and procedures for administering the petty cash funds.
11 C. 1. There is hereby created a petty cash fund in the finance
12 department of the Corporation Commission which shall be used solely
13 to pay litigation expenses of the legal division, including court
14 costs, filing fees, witness fees, and other expenses related to any
15 case, proceeding, or matter within the responsibility of the legal
16 division.
17 2. The Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
18 Services and the Corporation Commission are hereby authorized and it
19 shall be their duty to fix the maximum amount of the petty cash
20 fund, not to exceed Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00). The Director of
21 the Office of Management and Enterprise Services shall prescribe all
22 forms, systems, and procedures for administering the petty cash
23 fund.
24
