1 D. 1. There is hereby created a petty cash fund for the
2 Property Distribution Division of the Office of Management and
3 Enterprise Services.
4 2. The amount of the Property Distribution petty cash fund
5 shall not exceed Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00). The initial amount
6 shall be drawn by warrant from the State Surplus Property Revolving
7 Fund. The Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
8 Services is authorized to prescribe forms, systems and procedures
9 for the administration of the Property Distribution petty cash fund.
10 E. D. 1. There is hereby created a petty cash fund in the
11 legal division of the Oklahoma Health Care Authority which fund
12 shall be used solely to pay for court costs, filing fees, witness
13 fees, and expenses related to any case or proceeding within the
14 responsibility of the legal division.
15 2. The Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
16 Services and the Chief Executive Officer of the Oklahoma Health Care
17 Authority are hereby authorized and it shall be their duty to fix
18 the maximum amount of the petty cash fund, not to exceed Five
19 Hundred Dollars ($500.00). The Director of the Office of Management
20 and Enterprise Services shall prescribe all forms, systems, and
21 procedures for administering the petty cash fund.
22 F. E. 1. The Director of the Office of Management and
23 Enterprise Services is hereby authorized, upon request by the State
24 Commissioner of Health, to establish a petty cash fund for the State
